# Cline rules for blenderized-tubefeed-calculator

1. Read CONTEXT.md §9 (Current status) FIRST. Trust its checkboxes —
   do not re-do or re-verify completed phases.

2. The backend (data_loader, models, nutrients, calculator, intake,
   measures, targets, report) is COMPLETE and VERIFIED as of 2026-07-19
   (Intake Record rework — see CONTEXT.md §9). Do not rewrite,
   re-scaffold, or re-test these modules unless the user explicitly
   asks or a change breaks them. Reference data (nutrient registry,
   targets, formulas, thinning liquids) lives under data/packs/canada/,
   not data/targets/ or data/formulas/ — those directories no longer
   exist.

   **The single most important invariant to protect: there is
   deliberately NO "over-draw" / batch-mismatch flag anywhere in this
   app.** Daily totals are a direct sum over Intake Record rows
   (`src/intake.py::aggregate_intake()`) — never a schedule volume
   extrapolated against a blend's measured batch volume. That
   extrapolation was a real bug, fixed 2026-07-19; re-adding any
   "logged more than the batch made" check reintroduces it. Read
   `FEED_LOG_REWORK.md` §6.2 before touching `src/intake.py` or the
   Intake Record UI in `app/streamlit_app.py`.

3. To verify the backend, run:

   .venv/bin/python scripts/verify_backend.py

   It exits 0 and prints "=== ALL BACKEND MODULES VERIFIED ===" on
   success. If you add backend features, extend that script instead of
   writing a new one-off verification command. For UI changes, build
   a Streamlit AppTest script (see recent commits for the pattern) —
   "imports OK" alone does not prove a UI change works.

4. Current work: the app is feature-complete for its core loop (build
   blends → log an Intake Record spanning tube feed and oral intake →
   see live results). Remaining work is Week 3 scope (pytest suite, CI,
   Streamlit Cloud deploy, USDA SR Legacy supplement) plus the pinned
   issues in CONTEXT.md §9. See CONTEXT.md §1 for the app flow,
   FEED_LOG_REWORK.md for the Intake Record design rationale, and
   HANDOFF.md for a paste-ready prompt covering both.

5. Never modify anything under cnf_fcen_all-files-data_2026/ (raw data).

6. After completing meaningful work, update CONTEXT.md §9 status and
   commit, so the next session starts from accurate state.
